We were looking for a breakfast spot in the Bay Ridge. To my pleasant surprise, they had many great options! Cocoa Grinder is not a restaurant but more of a coffee shop that also serves healthy dishes. The inside is flooded with natural light, thanks to the floor-to-ceiling windows. They have a nice, relaxing, open space with good amount of seating.  We ordered a couple of different drinks. The first one was Grinders CoCoa. It was very nice cup of hot cocoa, silky smooth and velvety. I could taste the real cacao flavor, super tasty. Another one was Latte. At Cocoa Grinder, they roast their own coffee, so the quality and flavor was excellent.  As for food, we ordered Loxie Lox, Peanut Butter Banana Stuffed French Toast, and Poachy Poach. The omelette had a generous amount of smoked salmon, with perfect salty flavor. French Toast was a good portion, I liked how it was stacked like some pancakes. Poachy Poach was maybe the most simple item of all three. The amount of smoked salmon was not as much as I wanted… This item was the least exiting dish of all three. It was good, but it was just a-ok.  overall, we had a nice breakfast here with their health-conscious menu and tasty coffee. The staffs were nice and polite, and I enjoyed the relaxing atmosphere. Since they open early enough and have good amount of food menu, it is a nice breakfast spots when you are on the go.

Hell yeah! I have had Cocoa Grinder bookmarked for quite some time and last week had the chance to go twice for breakfast.  It is everything I heard about and then some. The restaurant has a total rustic yet modern classy feel. There is a wall full of books which makes it so inviting to sit, work and eat.  It is counter service so you order at the counter, pay there and they bring the food to the table. We ordered the standard french toast, mexican omellete, kale kraze wrap, lattes, frappes and fresh squeezed juice.  Everything we ordered was absolutely delightfully tasty and our plates were polished almost immediately. The chef keeps it simple and to the point which I love. The prices are also pretty decent and awesome perk if you check in with yelp you can get 20% off your bill (figured that one out when I checked in).  My only disappointment is the attitude of the employee at the counter who served me both times. It almost seemed like she didn't want to be there and that's a total turn off. It puts a damper on the experience.  Either way, I'll still return as the food is phenomenal so she can take her attitude elsewhere :). I totally recommend swinging by if you're ever in Bay Ridge.

Great neighborhood eatery for coffee, juice, and a variety of food! I come here with my girlfriends  every weekend after our yoga class and, so far, it has been consistently good. I always want to try something new, but I always end up ordering their Blackened Cajun Salmon Bowl, because it's so good! I usually get their Fat Burner juice, but I've also tried their Joint Helper Juice, and both are delicious and refreshing. Both are lightly sweetened, which is just the way I like it. My girlfriends like to get their coffees. One friend likes to get their breakfast sandwich of Eggs, Avocado, and Mozzarella, and my other girlfriend loves their Banana Chocolate Chip Pancakes and Classic Brioche French Toast, but was not fond of their turkey burger, which she said was very dry and had the texture of cardboard. We both gobbled up the sweet potato fries on her plate, though. They were hot and crispy. Perfectly cooked!  The decor is modern-industrial, with a bright and open layout. The walls are covered with varying types of reclaimed wood, and I love their living wall installments of real plants. It's a little tight getting around some of the tables when it's crowded, and the seating is not really made for comfort (strategic, I'm sure), but it's otherwise a great place to chill out and plug in your laptop, if you're so inclined, as they thoughtfully provided customers with many power outlets to plug in portable devices.
